BUILDING MODEL OF ANN¶

In [47]:
#importing tensor flow,dropout,callbacks
import tensorflow as tf
from tensorflow.keras.layers import Dropout
from keras import callbacks
In [48]:
#initialzing the ann
ann=tf.keras.models.Sequential()
In [49]:
#early stopping helps in stop the running epochs, when there is a best accuracy
early_stopping = callbacks.EarlyStopping(
    # minimium amount of change to count as an improvement
    min_delta=0.001,
    # how many epochs to wait before stopping
    patience=20, 
    restore_best_weights=True)
In [50]:
#using dense we can specify how many hidden neurons are needed and drop out of 20% neurons
ann.add(tf.keras.layers.Dense(units=12,kernel_initializer='uniform',activation='PReLU'))
ann.add(Dropout(0.2))
In [51]:
#using dense we can specify how many hidden neurons are needed and drop out of 50% neurons
ann.add(tf.keras.layers.Dense(units=6,kernel_initializer='uniform',activation='PReLU'))
ann.add(Dropout(0.5))
In [52]:
#binary  classification
output=ann.add(tf.keras.layers.Dense(units=1,activation='sigmoid'))
In [53]:
#compiling the model
ann.compile(optimizer = 'adam', loss = 'binary_crossentropy',metrics=['accuracy'])
In [54]:
#fitting the train data into ann model with batch size of 10, epochs =100 and also earlystopping
model=ann.fit(x_train, y_train,epochs=100,validation_split=0.33,batch_size=10,callbacks=early_stopping)
